    <chapter id="creating-charts"><title>Creating Charts</title>
        <para>When you first open &appName; you are presented with a blank window with a "New Chart Options" dialog at the top. This dialog gives you quick access to create a new document and chart. Form it you can set the basic informaiton about the new chart. If you select a Round chart the number of stitches is the number that is used on the inner most row. Subsequent rows will have increasing numbers of stitches. All of these values can be changed later while you edit the chart.</para>
        <screenshot>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata width="400" fileref="images/document-new.png" format="PNG" />
                </imageobject>
                <caption>The main window showing the New Chart Options dialog</caption>
            </mediaobject>
        </screenshot>
        <para>While editing the chart you can change the stitch, color, position, rotation, and height of the stitches, you can also add new stitches and new rows.
        </para>
